Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.52,0:00:25.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,Following on from "Nausicaä of the Valley of the Wind," \N"Arion," \Nand "Castle in the Sky"... \NTokuma's latest sci-fi anime!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.51,0:00:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,An invulnerable warrior, nicknamed "Death."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.45,0:00:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Grey.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.26,0:00:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 2588 AD.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.77,0:00:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,An enormous computer \Ndeveloped its own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.35,0:00:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The final battle for the survival \Nof humanity has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.15,0:01:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Gray's anger goes into overdrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.20,0:01:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Love, obsession, and unfettered rage \Nturned him into a God of Death.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.00,0:01:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A new type of endless battle action.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.58,0:01:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Grey: Digital Target.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.67,0:01:29.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord3\pos(348.63,295.51)}Grey commands this world and the afterlife {idfk what he means; 地獄の沙汰も\Nグレイしだい\N愛と怒りが死神と化す･････}\NLove and rage turned him into a God of Death.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.19,0:01:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Tagami Yoshihisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.56,0:01:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to ask you about Grey.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.03,0:01:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the incentive, \Nthe starting point for Grey?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.39,0:01:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.16,0:01:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to draw science fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.11,0:01:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, so it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.50,0:01:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But I also didn't want it to be a plain \Nsci-fi that was all the rage at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.20,0:02:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What I mean is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With mechas coming out \Nand snapping to a giant battle scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.19,0:02:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wanted to draw \Nsomething different for a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.93,0:02:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Something no one else \Nwould have the folly to draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.35,0:02:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So one day I sat myself down \Nand started drawing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.75,0:02:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let me sum it up, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.54,0:02:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.31,0:02:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You just had the urge to draw science fiction \Nand Grey was born from that wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.81,0:02:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And about his name—Grey—\Nis there any meaning to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.72,0:02:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Not particularly, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.97,0:02:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a normal name, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.57,0:02:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It just... How to put it? \NI think it sort of fitted my vision of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.54,0:02:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in other words, he's an "SF hero" \Nbefore anything else, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.94,0:02:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. I just felt that since he's the protagonist, I might as well make his name the title.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.82,0:02:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That was my logic behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.93,0:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There are various mechas \Nappearing in your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.78,0:03:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of them sound like their names were inspired by Buddhism, such as Kubanda and Ohm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.06,0:03:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You must've consulted \Na lot of historical records for it? {idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.02,0:03:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.42,0:03:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you just did it by feel? {think she means "named them so because it sounded buddhist"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.97,0:03:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinda.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.71,0:03:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Not sure how I did it, \NI think I just liked how it sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.61,0:03:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.94,0:03:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I did it by feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.12,0:03:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because I'm a devout believer \Nor something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.18,0:03:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a believer. So you just thought to yourself \N"Kubanda, Ohm, yeah I like how it rings"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, sounds about right.\N- So that was your process?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.23,0:03:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Story.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.18,0:03:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The year is 2588 AD.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.84,0:03:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanity is ruled \Nby the central government—"Big Mama."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.44,0:03:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,People were divided into six classes, \Nfrom Class A to Class F.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the privileged elites of Class A, \Nthe Citizens, are guaranteed their right to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the population is made up \Nof the lowest classes, "the People."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.53,0:04:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To advance to Citizens, \Npeople have to become warriors called Troupers,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.96,0:04:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and fight for their survival \Nin an endless war against other towns.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.41,0:04:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,However, of the lowest, class F, Troupers, \Nonly 0.3% live long enough to advance to Class A.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In that age, an immortal warrior appears, \Nfeared by his enemies and his allies alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.25,0:04:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is "Grey the Death."
